
Overview of adv softly

The adv softly has 4 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (18) softly, quietly -- (with low volume; "speak softly but carry a big stick"; "she spoke quietly to the child"; "the radio was playing softly")
2. (3) softly -- (in a manner that is pleasing to the senses; "she smiled softly")
3. (3) lightly, softly, gently -- (with little weight or force; "she kissed him lightly on the forehead")
4. piano, softly -- (used as a direction in music; to be played relatively softly)
